ing grand maxima is indicated, but it cannot\nbe separated from the main component in a statistically significant manner. A\nnew consistent reconstruction of solar activity over the last nine millennia is\npresented with the most probable values of decadal sunspot numbers and their\nrealistic uncertainties. Independent components of solar activity corresponding\nto the main moderate activity and the grand-minimum state are identified; they\nmay be related to different operation modes of the dynamo.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 4 Apr 2018 08:50:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-07-25"}
